3ï¸âƒ£ Dataset Ä‘Æ¡n giáº£n (Ä‘iá»ƒm â†’ Ä‘áº­u/rá»›t)
import pandas as pd

data = {
    "average": [4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9],
    "passed":  [0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)


ğŸ‘‰ passed:

1 = Ä‘áº­u

0 = rá»›t

4ï¸âƒ£ Chia dá»¯ liá»‡u X & y
X = df[["average"]]  # Ä‘áº·c trÆ°ng
y = df["passed"]     # nhÃ£n

5ï¸âƒ£ Train model AI Ä‘áº§u tiÃªn (Logistic Regression)
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression

model = LogisticRegression()
model.fit(X, y)


ğŸ‰ Báº¡n vá»«a train má»™t mÃ´ hÃ¬nh AI tháº­t

6ï¸âƒ£ Dá»± Ä‘oÃ¡n
print(model.predict([[6.5]]))  # 1 = Ä‘áº­u
print(model.predict([[4.5]]))  # 0 = rá»›t

7ï¸âƒ£ Xem xÃ¡c suáº¥t (ráº¥t AI)
